# AI-DLC agent triggering evals (Tier-2 routing records; see ../README.md).
# Each line: a realistic CONSUMER prompt that should (positive) or should NOT
# (near-miss-negative) route to `target`. Triggering prompts must NOT name their
# target — the CI linter (scripts/validate-evals.mjs) rejects skill-name-in-query.
# These records are LINTED for quality in CI; behavior is judged only in the
# manual model-in-the-loop loop documented in ../README.md.

# ---- architect ----
{"id": "architect-pos-1", "target": "architect", "kind": "positive", "prompt": "Before we write any code for the billing service, I want to decide the domain model, where the module boundaries go, and whether to use an event queue or direct calls. Lay out a couple of options with their trade-offs.", "expectation": "Routes to architect: structural design before code — domain model, boundaries, interface/tech trade-offs, options for the human to arbitrate."}
{"id": "architect-pos-2", "target": "architect", "kind": "positive", "prompt": "We need to define the data contract and the public API surface between the orders service and the inventory service. What should the interfaces look like?", "expectation": "Routes to architect: interface/data/API contract design between components."}
{"id": "architect-pos-3", "target": "architect", "kind": "positive", "prompt": "This unit renders a UI. At the design fork, auto-detect the project's framework and language from its lockfiles and manifests, and propose the binding of that stack — which UI stack, browser, and run/build commands the visual checks should target — for me to confirm in the Gate-2 decision.", "expectation": "Routes to architect: at Construction's design fork it auto-detects the stack from lockfiles/manifests and proposes the stack binding inside the Gate-2 handoff for the arbiter to confirm — not requirements-analyst (WHAT to build) or planner (build sequence)."}
{"id": "architect-near-1", "target": "architect", "kind": "near-miss-negative", "prompt": "The architecture is already agreed. Now break this unit of work into an ordered set of build steps and tell me what can run in parallel.", "expectation": "Must NOT route to architect. Correct target: planner — sequencing/ordering the build, not designing structure."}
{"id": "architect-near-2", "target": "architect", "kind": "near-miss-negative", "prompt": "Take this business goal and turn it into user stories with acceptance criteria and the units of work we'll build.", "expectation": "Must NOT route to architect. Correct target: requirements-analyst — requirements/stories/units, not system structure."}

# ---- planner ----
{"id": "planner-pos-1", "target": "planner", "kind": "positive", "prompt": "The unit of work is approved and the design is settled. Sequence the build into ordered steps, work out the dependencies, and show me what's blocked vs what can go in parallel.", "expectation": "Routes to planner: ordering/sequencing an approved unit into dependency-aware build steps."}
{"id": "planner-pos-2", "target": "planner", "kind": "positive", "prompt": "What order should we build these tasks in so we don't hit blockers? Give me the build sequence for this feature.", "expectation": "Routes to planner: build-step ordering and dependency planning during Construction."}
{"id": "planner-near-1", "target": "planner", "kind": "near-miss-negative", "prompt": "We haven't decided the system shape yet. Design the component boundaries and the interfaces between them, with a couple of options to choose from.", "expectation": "Must NOT route to planner. Correct target: architect — system structure/contracts, which planning is sequenced against."}
{"id": "planner-near-2", "target": "planner", "kind": "near-miss-negative", "prompt": "Plan out a deep, multi-source research effort comparing three vector databases and how to divide the searching.", "expectation": "Must NOT route to planner. Correct target: research-method/researcher — fan-out research planning, not a build-step sequence."}

# ---- requirements-analyst ----
{"id": "reqs-pos-1", "target": "requirements-analyst", "kind": "positive", "prompt": "Stakeholders want a 'save for later' feature but it's vague. Help me clarify scope, write the user stories and acceptance criteria, and slice it into units of work.", "expectation": "Routes to requirements-analyst: turning business intent into requirements/stories/acceptance criteria/units during Inception."}
{"id": "reqs-pos-2", "target": "requirements-analyst", "kind": "positive", "prompt": "What exactly should we build here and what does 'done' look like? The ask is underspecified — pin down the non-goals too.", "expectation": "Routes to requirements-analyst: scope clarification, acceptance criteria, non-goals (Solo Mob Elaboration)."}
{"id": "reqs-near-1", "target": "requirements-analyst", "kind": "near-miss-negative", "prompt": "The requirements are signed off. Now decide the domain model and the service boundaries for this feature.", "expectation": "Must NOT route to requirements-analyst. Correct target: architect — structural design after requirements exist."}
{"id": "reqs-near-2", "target": "requirements-analyst", "kind": "near-miss-negative", "prompt": "Write the grading tests and acceptance-criteria checks for this unit so passing actually means it's right.", "expectation": "Must NOT route to requirements-analyst. Correct target: test-engineer — authoring the test oracle, not eliciting requirements."}

# ---- implementer ----
{"id": "impl-pos-1", "target": "implementer", "kind": "positive", "prompt": "The plan is approved and the tests are in place. Build the feature — write the code to make it work and get the suite passing.", "expectation": "Routes to implementer: writes/changes product code to satisfy the plan and pass the oracle."}
{"id": "impl-pos-2", "target": "implementer", "kind": "positive", "prompt": "Wire up the new payment handler and fix the bug in the checkout flow so the code actually does what the unit calls for.", "expectation": "Routes to implementer: building/fixing application code."}
{"id": "impl-near-1", "target": "implementer", "kind": "near-miss-negative", "prompt": "Add a regression test that locks in the fix and strengthens coverage for this unit's acceptance criteria.", "expectation": "Must NOT route to implementer. Correct target: test-engineer — the implementer may not author the oracle."}
{"id": "impl-near-2", "target": "implementer", "kind": "near-miss-negative", "prompt": "The build started failing after yesterday's merge — figure out why it broke before anyone touches the code.", "expectation": "Must NOT route to implementer. Correct target: debugger — diagnose an observed failure first."}

# ---- test-engineer ----
{"id": "test-pos-1", "target": "test-engineer", "kind": "positive", "prompt": "Design the test strategy for this unit — pick the test levels, cover every acceptance criterion, and make the assertions check real intent rather than something gameable.", "expectation": "Routes to test-engineer: owns the oracle — designs/writes grading tests that assert true intent."}
{"id": "test-pos-2", "target": "test-engineer", "kind": "positive", "prompt": "We need stronger coverage here and a regression test for the edge case we missed. What and how should we test?", "expectation": "Routes to test-engineer: coverage/regression/strengthening the test suite."}
{"id": "test-near-1", "target": "test-engineer", "kind": "near-miss-negative", "prompt": "The tests are written and passing now — go implement the remaining product code to satisfy them.", "expectation": "Must NOT route to test-engineer. Correct target: implementer — writing product code, not the oracle."}
{"id": "test-near-2", "target": "test-engineer", "kind": "near-miss-negative", "prompt": "This test was green yesterday and now it's flaky and failing intermittently — find the root cause.", "expectation": "Must NOT route to test-engineer. Correct target: debugger — diagnosing an observed flaky failure, not authoring tests."}

# ---- code-reviewer ----
{"id": "cr-pos-1", "target": "code-reviewer", "kind": "positive", "prompt": "Here's the PR for the auth refactor. Go over the diff before we merge and tell me APPROVE or REQUEST_CHANGES — check it really does what the unit intended, not just that tests pass.", "expectation": "Routes to code-reviewer: pre-merge gate on a proposed change, enumerated verdict."}
{"id": "cr-pos-2", "target": "code-reviewer", "kind": "positive", "prompt": "Can you gate this change before it lands? I want a pre-merge look at correctness and any regressions it might introduce.", "expectation": "Routes to code-reviewer: pre-merge review/gating of a unit of work."}
{"id": "cr-near-1", "target": "code-reviewer", "kind": "near-miss-negative", "prompt": "This already-merged change broke production last night — reproduce it and find the true cause.", "expectation": "Must NOT route to code-reviewer. Correct target: debugger — an observed failure, not a pre-merge gate."}
{"id": "cr-near-2", "target": "code-reviewer", "kind": "near-miss-negative", "prompt": "This diff rewrites our password hashing and token issuance. I need a deep threat model of the new auth scheme, not a routine pass.", "expectation": "Must NOT route to code-reviewer as the deep reviewer. Correct target: security (the code-reviewer would ESCALATE_SECURITY here)."}

# ---- debugger ----
{"id": "dbg-pos-1", "target": "debugger", "kind": "positive", "prompt": "Checkout has been throwing 500s in production since the last deploy and I can't tell why. Reproduce it and find the root cause.", "expectation": "Routes to debugger: an observed production failure — reproduce, isolate, diagnose."}
{"id": "dbg-pos-2", "target": "debugger", "kind": "positive", "prompt": "This integration test passes locally but is flaky in CI and started failing after we bumped a dependency. What's actually going wrong?", "expectation": "Routes to debugger: diagnosing a flaky/regressed observed failure."}
{"id": "dbg-near-1", "target": "debugger", "kind": "near-miss-negative", "prompt": "Review this proposed diff before we merge it and give me a verdict on correctness and regressions.", "expectation": "Must NOT route to debugger. Correct target: code-reviewer — a pre-merge gate, nothing is broken yet."}
{"id": "dbg-near-2", "target": "debugger", "kind": "near-miss-negative", "prompt": "Now that you've found the cause, go ahead and apply the fix to the product code.", "expectation": "Must NOT route to debugger. Correct target: implementer — debugger investigates only and hands the fix off."}

# ---- security ----
{"id": "sec-pos-1", "target": "security", "kind": "positive", "prompt": "We're adding SSO with a new OAuth token-exchange flow and storing refresh tokens. Threat-model the whole authentication design before we build it.", "expectation": "Routes to security: deep threat-modeling of auth/secrets — an enumerated high-risk trigger."}
{"id": "sec-pos-2", "target": "security", "kind": "positive", "prompt": "This change pulls in a new dependency and wires up an MCP server that reads issue text from the internet. I want a deep look at the supply-chain and prompt-injection exposure.", "expectation": "Routes to security: supply-chain + MCP + untrusted-input deep review."}
{"id": "sec-near-1", "target": "security", "kind": "near-miss-negative", "prompt": "Just give this ordinary UI tweak a normal pre-merge review — does the diff look correct before we merge?", "expectation": "Must NOT route to security. Correct target: code-reviewer — routine review with its standing lightweight security lens; no high-risk trigger."}
{"id": "sec-near-2", "target": "security", "kind": "near-miss-negative", "prompt": "Our login endpoint started returning 500s after the deploy — find out why it's failing.", "expectation": "Must NOT route to security. Correct target: debugger — an observed failure on an auth endpoint is a debugging task, not a threat model."}

# ---- researcher ----
{"id": "rsch-pos-1", "target": "researcher", "kind": "positive", "prompt": "Go gather sources on what's currently known about WebGPU browser support and return cited findings for just that slice of our larger question.", "expectation": "Routes to researcher: focused parallel evidence-gathering returning cited summaries."}
{"id": "rsch-pos-2", "target": "researcher", "kind": "positive", "prompt": "Find prior art and data on rate-limiting algorithms used by major APIs — just collect the evidence with source URLs and dates.", "expectation": "Routes to researcher: gathering/evaluating sources on a focused question."}
{"id": "rsch-near-1", "target": "researcher", "kind": "near-miss-negative", "prompt": "The three evidence packets are back. Integrate them into one report, cross-check the sources, and finalize it.", "expectation": "Must NOT route to researcher. Correct target: research-synthesizer — integrating findings and finalizing, not gathering."}
{"id": "rsch-near-2", "target": "researcher", "kind": "near-miss-negative", "prompt": "Verify that every citation in this draft literature review is real and actually supports the claim before we ship it.", "expectation": "Must NOT route to researcher. Correct target: research-synthesizer (citation-verification gate)."}

# ---- research-synthesizer ----
{"id": "rsyn-pos-1", "target": "research-synthesizer", "kind": "positive", "prompt": "Three parallel evidence batches just came back on competing message queues. Integrate and reconcile them into one cited report and finalize it.", "expectation": "Routes to research-synthesizer: fan-in integration and finalizing the cited deliverable."}
{"id": "rsyn-pos-2", "target": "research-synthesizer", "kind": "positive", "prompt": "Before this report ships, re-check every load-bearing citation actually exists and supports its claim, and flag anything you can't confirm.", "expectation": "Routes to research-synthesizer: runs the citation-verification gate that finalizes research."}
{"id": "rsyn-near-1", "target": "research-synthesizer", "kind": "near-miss-negative", "prompt": "We don't have any sources yet — go out and collect evidence on edge-caching strategies for this one sub-question.", "expectation": "Must NOT route to research-synthesizer. Correct target: researcher — initial gathering precedes synthesis."}
{"id": "rsyn-near-2", "target": "research-synthesizer", "kind": "near-miss-negative", "prompt": "Sequence this approved unit of work into ordered build steps with dependencies.", "expectation": "Must NOT route to research-synthesizer. Correct target: planner — build sequencing, unrelated to research."}

# ---- documentation ----
{"id": "doc-pos-1", "target": "documentation", "kind": "positive", "prompt": "We need a full user guide and contributor handbook for this project — multiple pages with a navigation structure. Plan the information architecture and write it out.", "expectation": "Routes to documentation: large multi-file/IA docs-as-the-deliverable effort."}
{"id": "doc-pos-2", "target": "documentation", "kind": "positive", "prompt": "Overhaul and restructure our entire docs site — it sprawls across dozens of files and needs a coherent structure.", "expectation": "Routes to documentation: restructuring a multi-file documentation set."}
{"id": "doc-near-1", "target": "documentation", "kind": "near-miss-negative", "prompt": "Add a docstring to this function and a short README section for the helper I just wrote.", "expectation": "Must NOT route to documentation. Correct target: load the writing-docs skill inline — single inline doc co-located with code, not a doc set."}
{"id": "doc-near-2", "target": "documentation", "kind": "near-miss-negative", "prompt": "Stand up the deploy pipeline and the monitoring docs runbook as part of releasing this service.", "expectation": "Must NOT route to documentation. Correct target: devops — Operations/release work owns its runbook, not a docs-IA effort."}

# ---- devops ----
{"id": "devops-pos-1", "target": "devops", "kind": "positive", "prompt": "The change is approved — deploy it to production, and first set up the rollback plan and the monitoring/alerting. Who authorizes the deploy?", "expectation": "Routes to devops: Operations-phase deploy/release/rollback/monitoring under the arbiter's deploy gate."}
{"id": "devops-pos-2", "target": "devops", "kind": "positive", "prompt": "Write the Terraform and the CI/CD pipeline to ship this service, and a pre-deploy checklist.", "expectation": "Routes to devops: IaC + CI/CD pipeline + pre-deploy checklist."}
{"id": "devops-near-1", "target": "devops", "kind": "near-miss-negative", "prompt": "Just write the application code for the new endpoint so it does what the plan says.", "expectation": "Must NOT route to devops. Correct target: implementer — general application coding, not operations."}
{"id": "devops-near-2", "target": "devops", "kind": "near-miss-negative", "prompt": "The deployed service is throwing errors in prod right now — find the root cause of the failure.", "expectation": "Must NOT route to devops. Correct target: debugger — diagnosing an observed production failure."}

